JAR applications exported currently adopt a file name duke.jar.

The chatbot's name is not Duke anymore, but Moira.

commitResults.messageTitle: Modify code to adhere to coding standards
commitResults.messageBody:
The code has clear violations of coding standard.

This makes the code look unprofessional.

Now the code mostly adheres to the coding standards.

More edits will be made when making changes to improve code quality.

commitResults.messageTitle: Improve the code quality in all classes
commitResults.messageBody:
The code has a lot of code quality issues, most notably deep nesting and missing default cases,
causing the code to be very hard to follow, unreadable and unsafe.

Refactoring the code in compliance with code quality guidelines will help make the code
more reader-friendly and accessible for other programmers.

Let's,
- Remove deep nesting in Parser class to make the happy path more noticeable
- Change boolean names to sound more like booleans (e.g. done to isDone)
- Simplify complex statements involving conditional operators
- Add the default case to the switch block in the Storage class

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Java assertions in Duke, Parser and Storage classes
commitResults.messageBody:
The code runs under certain important assumptions that are currently unchecked.

Adding assertions at various points in the code can detect potential runtime errors
arising from mistakes that programmers have made in the code.

Let's make use of the Java assert feature to increase the safety of our code.

Add sort task list functionality to chat bot
commitResults.messageBody:
The current chat bot manages a list with tasks in the order of
the date they were added.

Allowing users to sort their task list by a specified sort
order can help them better organize their tasks.

Let's,
- Add a command to sort the task list
- Allow sorting by description, deadline(date) or task type

Representing sort order using a nested enum in the
TaskList class allows for easy reference of
available sort order types from other classes and
maintains encapsulation of information related to sorting.
